honline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27566,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/15\/permission-not-fast-journey\/","url_meta":{"origin":28698,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Permission to fast or not on journey, whatever is easiest","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 15, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: Hamzah ibn Amr asked the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, about fasting while traveling. The Prophet said, \u201cIf you wish, you may fast. And if you wish, you may break your fast.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1841, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1121 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3756,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/23\/ramadan-do-not-precede-fast\/","url_meta":{"origin":28698,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Do not fast days before Ramadan, unless a routine","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 23, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cLet not one of you precede Ramadan with one or two days of fasting, unless it is part of a man's fasting routine, so let him fast that day.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1815. S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1082\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4035,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/03\/fasting-haram-eid-fitr-adha-tashriq\/","url_meta":{"origin":28698,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Eid: The Prophet forbids fasting on the two Eids","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 3, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu 'Ubayd reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cO people, the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, has prohibited you from fasting on the days of these two celebrations, Eid al-Fitr and Eid al-Adha. One of them is the day you break\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3761,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/23\/prophet-observed-wasala-fasting\/","url_meta":{"origin":28698,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: The Prophet continuously fasted, Muslims may not","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 23, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would observe continuous fasting during the month of Ramadan and so did the people, but he prohibited them. It was said, \u201cYou are continuously fasting.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cVerily, I am not like you, for I am\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3795,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/24\/accidentally-break-fast-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":28698,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: One who accidentally breaks fast completes it","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 24, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever eats or drinks forgetfully while he is fasting, let him complete his fast, for Allah has fed him and given him drink.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1933, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1155 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/28698","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=28698"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/28698\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=28698"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=28698"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaeli